1
00:00:02.798 --> 00:00:04.158  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( door opens )

2
00:00:05.517 --> 00:00:07.157  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( door closes )

3
00:00:09.836 --> 00:00:11.395  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I didn't expect to find you here.

4
00:00:12.361 --> 00:00:13.595  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I thought you'd be down on the Promenade

5
00:00:13.675 --> 00:00:17.744  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
helping Mardah put up the decorations
for the Bajoran Gratitude Festival.

6
00:00:17.713 --> 00:00:19.473  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That was the plan

7
00:00:19.993 --> 00:00:22.712  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but it turns out I don't have
much to be grateful for.

8
00:00:23.551 --> 00:00:27.091  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Isn't that the earring you--
-Bought for Mardah, yeah. You want it?

9
00:00:27.111 --> 00:00:29.910  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe you can give it to Major Kira
for her next birthday or something.

10
00:00:30.589 --> 00:00:32.829  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs ) All right.

11
00:00:32.909 --> 00:00:34.389  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tell me about it.

12
00:00:36.588 --> 00:00:38.682  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mardah's gone, Dad.

13
00:00:38.628 --> 00:00:41.546  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She got accepted to the Science Academy
on Regulus III.

14
00:00:41.826 --> 00:00:42.986  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's a good school.

15
00:00:43.662 --> 00:00:45.186  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's 300 light-years away.

16
00:00:45.265 --> 00:00:47.145  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jake, you're 16.

17
00:00:47.225 --> 00:00:49.424  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Take my word for it, you'll survive.

18
00:00:50.144 --> 00:00:52.103  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sooner or later, you'll find someone else.

19
00:00:52.543 --> 00:00:53.383  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who knows?

20
00:00:53.463 --> 00:00:56.222  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe you'll find someone tonight
at the Gratitude Festival.

21
00:00:56.702 --> 00:00:57.902  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah, sure.

22
00:00:57.982 --> 00:00:59.622  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jake, the whole point of the festival

23
00:00:59.701 --> 00:01:02.820  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is to put all your troubles behind you
and make a new start.

24
00:01:03.260 --> 00:01:04.700  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I could use one.

25
00:01:05.819 --> 00:01:08.819  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-OK, I'll go.
-Good. That's the spirit.

26
00:01:09.658 --> 00:01:11.337  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But I'm not going to have any fun.

27
00:01:12.297 --> 00:01:13.417  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh.

28
00:01:16.376 --> 00:01:17.895  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( laughs ) Nervous, Chief?

29
00:01:18.656 --> 00:01:20.175  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( laughs )

30
00:01:20.614 --> 00:01:21.495  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you talking about?

31
00:01:21.574 --> 00:01:23.773  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's your fifth cup of coffee
in 20 minutes.

32
00:01:24.174 --> 00:01:25.773  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I didn't realize you were keeping track.

33
00:01:25.853 --> 00:01:27.892  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, nervous and irascible.

34
00:01:27.973 --> 00:01:30.372  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If you hadn't seen your wife
and child for two months,

35
00:01:30.452 --> 00:01:31.491  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
you'd be irascible, too.

36
00:01:31.572 --> 00:01:32.731  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, believe me, I'm looking forward

37
00:01:32.812 --> 00:01:34.371  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to Keiko and Molly's visit
as much as you are.

38
00:01:34.451 --> 00:01:35.651  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I doubt that.

39
00:01:35.730 --> 00:01:39.209  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
How many games of racquetball
have we played in the last two months?

40
00:01:39.289 --> 00:01:41.529  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't know. 15, maybe 20.

41
00:01:41.608 --> 00:01:42.968  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, try 70.

42
00:01:43.487 --> 00:01:44.528  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've been keeping track of that, too.

43
00:01:44.608 --> 00:01:46.407  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know what all those games
have proved to me?

44
00:01:46.487 --> 00:01:48.766  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That I'm a poor substitute for your wife.

45
00:01:49.407 --> 00:01:51.605  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I could have told you that 60 games ago.

46
00:01:52.885 --> 00:01:55.484  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Thing is, they're only going
to be here for two days.

47
00:01:55.565 --> 00:01:57.204  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's barely enough time to say hello.

48
00:01:57.284 --> 00:02:00.838  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And they're back to Bajor again
for another four months.

49
00:02:00.403 --> 00:02:02.243  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Four months?

50
00:02:02.322 --> 00:02:04.482  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why, that's another
150 games of racquetball.

51
00:02:04.561 --> 00:02:07.141  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't think my elbow
can take that kind of abuse.

52
00:02:07.161 --> 00:02:09.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe you can try
and convince her to stay.

53
00:02:09.360 --> 00:02:10.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, no, I can't do that.

54
00:02:10.760 --> 00:02:12.395  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I mean, I'm the one who suggested she go

55
00:02:12.120 --> 00:02:14.399  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
on this agrobiology expedition
in the first place.

56
00:02:15.358 --> 00:02:18.158  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No, we'll just have to make
the best of the little time we have.

57
00:02:18.797 --> 00:02:21.956  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Which means we can't waste
a second of the next two days.

58
00:02:33.390 --> 00:02:35.490  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah, <i>peldor joi, </i>Odo.

59
00:02:35.512 --> 00:02:38.152  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Peldor joi </i>to you, too, Major.

60
00:02:33.230 --> 00:02:33.370  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well...

61
00:02:40.511 --> 00:02:42.110  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's, uh...

62
00:02:42.550 --> 00:02:46.269  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's hard to believe
the Promenade is this empty at midday.

63
00:02:46.349 --> 00:02:48.629  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, calm before the storm.

64
00:02:48.708 --> 00:02:53.387  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
In a few hours, this place will be packed
with Bajorans celebrating the festival.

65
00:02:54.507 --> 00:02:59.225  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Actually, I was thinking
of joining you this year.

66
00:02:59.306 --> 00:03:00.185  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Really?

67
00:03:00.265 --> 00:03:01.745  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't see why not.

68
00:03:01.824 --> 00:03:04.983  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
None of my Bajoran deputies
work during the Gratitude Festival.

69
00:03:05.643 --> 00:03:06.703  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why should I?

70
00:03:06.783 --> 00:03:10.662  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Besides, if I'm going to
live here with you humanoids

71
00:03:10.742 --> 00:03:14.420  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I may as well immerse myself
in your rituals.

72
00:03:14.501 --> 00:03:15.609  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, then, we'll see each other later.

73
00:03:12.860 --> 00:03:13.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'd like that.

74
00:03:14.699 --> 00:03:15.789  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If you're not too busy
being the Presider at the festival.

75
00:03:18.578 --> 00:03:21.518  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
For you, I will make the time, Odo.

76
00:03:21.538 --> 00:03:23.896  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just look for me. I'll be with Bareil.

77
00:03:24.697 --> 00:03:25.816  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh...

78
00:03:49.069 --> 00:03:53.228  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I thought he'd be celebrating
the festival on Bajor.

79
00:03:30.735 --> 00:03:32.454  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So did I. I'm glad I was wrong.

80
00:03:32.534 --> 00:03:33.814  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's arriving on the next shuttle.

81
00:03:45.810 --> 00:03:49.049  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well... you'd better go.
It'll be here soon.

82
00:03:15.629 --> 00:03:15.790  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're right.

83
00:03:15.810 --> 00:03:45.790  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I'll see you at the festival.
-Ah.

84
00:03:56.912 --> 00:03:57.287  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Chief.

85
00:03:57.366 --> 00:03:59.705  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Major.

86
00:03:59.446 --> 00:04:01.925  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Keiko.
-Ah... Bareil.

87
00:04:02.445 --> 00:04:05.244  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Good luck.
-You, too.

88
00:04:11.393 --> 00:04:12.562  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nerys...`

89
00:04:12.762 --> 00:04:14.562  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I am so glad to see you.

90
00:04:14.641 --> 00:04:15.881  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I missed you.

91
00:04:15.961 --> 00:04:17.601  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I missed you, too.

92
00:04:24.039 --> 00:04:25.238  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Miles.

93
00:04:25.318 --> 00:04:26.798  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Miles!

94
00:04:26.878 --> 00:04:28.819  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, Keiko.

95
00:04:29.396 --> 00:04:31.177  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm so glad to see you.

96
00:04:31.197 --> 00:04:33.316  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have had the worst trip.

97
00:04:33.396 --> 00:04:36.396  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, really? I'm sorry to hear that.

98
00:04:36.155 --> 00:04:38.155  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Now that you're here
everything's going to be great.

99
00:04:39.194 --> 00:04:40.673  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hello, sweetie.

100
00:04:40.754 --> 00:04:42.714  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You ready to have
a great time with your dad?

101
00:04:42.793 --> 00:04:43.793  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

102
00:04:44.473 --> 00:04:45.313  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why not?

103
00:04:45.552 --> 00:04:47.712  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't feel so good.

104
00:04:47.792 --> 00:04:48.872  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Really?

105
00:04:48.951 --> 00:04:51.390  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Aw... tell Daddy what's wrong.

106
00:04:51.910 --> 00:04:53.350  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-( retching )
-Ah!

107
00:04:53.430 --> 00:04:54.989  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( gasps ) Oh...

108
00:04:55.349 --> 00:04:57.428  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
LWAXANA: Oh... you poor dear.

109
00:04:58.628 --> 00:05:00.748  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I should never have given you
all that candy.

110
00:06:55.913 --> 00:06:58.512  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I usually make it a point
to drop by Quark's

111
00:06:58.592 --> 00:07:01.357  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
three or four times a day
at random intervals.

112
00:07:01.152 --> 00:07:03.911  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Just to let him know
I'm thinking about him

113
00:07:03.991 --> 00:07:08.710  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
but seeing today is a holiday
he'll be busier than usual.

114
00:07:08.789 --> 00:07:12.228  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I suggest you station
a man there full time.

115
00:07:12.308 --> 00:07:13.428  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I think that about covers it.

116
00:07:13.508 --> 00:07:15.187  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
If you need me, I'll be on the Promenade.

117
00:07:15.268 --> 00:07:17.786  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
LWAXANA: But don't call
unless it's an emergency.

118
00:07:18.826 --> 00:07:20.746  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
The Constable will be occupied.

119
00:07:21.466 --> 00:07:23.505  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
ODO: Madam Ambassador.

120
00:07:24.185 --> 00:07:27.704  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Oh, do we have to be so formal?

121
00:07:32.583 --> 00:07:35.621  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Didn't they teach you any manners
in Starfleet Academy?

122
00:07:35.701 --> 00:07:38.121  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Be a dear, run along.

123
00:07:38.141 --> 00:07:40.900  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
The Constable and I have
a lot of catching up to do.

124
00:07:40.979 --> 00:07:42.699  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Uh, come back in five minutes.

125
00:07:42.779 --> 00:07:44.619  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Make that half an hour.

126
00:07:47.697 --> 00:07:49.178  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
So...

127
00:07:51.019 --> 00:07:52.017  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
what brings you to the station?

128
00:07:52.336 --> 00:07:53.656  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, officially I'm here

129
00:07:53.736 --> 00:07:56.855  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
as the Betazoid representative
to the Gratitude Festival

130
00:07:56.935 --> 00:08:02.773  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but the truth is, I came to see you,
you poor, sweet, tortured man.

131
00:08:03.613 --> 00:08:04.773  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Excuse me?

132
00:08:04.852 --> 00:08:07.892  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, well, I know the torment
you must be going through.

133
00:08:07.971 --> 00:08:10.491  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, to spend your whole life searching
for your people,

134
00:08:10.570 --> 00:08:14.650  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
only to discover that they're the leaders
of that awful Dominion.

135
00:08:15.529 --> 00:08:16.729  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You heard about that.

136
00:08:16.809 --> 00:08:18.008  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Odo...

137
00:08:18.408 --> 00:08:19.728  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
don't worry.

138
00:08:20.447 --> 00:08:21.887  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm here to help you.

139
00:08:22.407 --> 00:08:24.846  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What kind of help do you mean?

140
00:08:25.246 --> 00:08:28.165  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, a sympathetic ear...

141
00:08:28.246 --> 00:08:30.405  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
a shoulder to cry on...

142
00:08:30.485 --> 00:08:32.244  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
a lap to melt in.

143
00:08:32.924 --> 00:08:33.924  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah.

144
00:08:34.284 --> 00:08:37.963  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, that's very considerate of you,
but unnecessary.

145
00:08:38.402 --> 00:08:40.242  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My people are who they are.

146
00:08:40.321 --> 00:08:41.321  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I am who I am.

147
00:08:41.402 --> 00:08:42.841  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've learned to accept that.

148
00:08:43.401 --> 00:08:45.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, you brave soul.

149
00:08:46.720 --> 00:08:52.158  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, why don't we go someplace quiet
and you can tell me all about it?

150
00:08:52.718 --> 00:08:55.437  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Actually, I was planning
to attend the opening

151
00:08:55.518 --> 00:08:57.397  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
of the Gratitude Festival this afternoon.

152
00:08:57.997 --> 00:08:58.996  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh...

153
00:08:59.410 --> 00:09:00.836  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, even better.

154
00:09:00.915 --> 00:09:03.955  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
First, a little fun and relaxation

155
00:09:04.035 --> 00:09:08.794  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and then we can delve
into the depths of your pain.

156
00:09:08.873 --> 00:09:12.152  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'll freshen up and meet you
in front of the Bajoran Temple

157
00:09:12.233 --> 00:09:14.592  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
for the Presider's opening address.

158
00:09:16.951 --> 00:09:21.230  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I promise you, Odo,
you'll never be alone again.

159
00:09:29.867 --> 00:09:31.711  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( beep )

160
00:09:35.386 --> 00:09:36.905  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Level 23, Section 8.

161
00:09:37.385 --> 00:09:38.464  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh!

162
00:09:42.982 --> 00:09:45.162  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We need to see each other more often.

163
00:09:45.182 --> 00:09:48.422  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm, I wish we both weren't so busy.

164
00:09:53.220 --> 00:09:57.378  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I never expected Kai Winn to make me
one of her principal advisors.

165
00:09:57.459 --> 00:09:59.178  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I think she asks your advice

166
00:09:59.259 --> 00:10:02.817  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
just so that she can do the exact opposite
of what you recommend.

167
00:10:02.897 --> 00:10:07.176  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I know you don't like Winn
but the office has changed her.

168
00:10:07.896 --> 00:10:09.535  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Prophets chose well.

169
00:10:10.775 --> 00:10:16.213  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So, why don't we leave
spiritual matters in their capable hands

170
00:10:16.293 --> 00:10:20.192  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and uh, concentrate on enjoying ourselves?

171
00:10:20.212 --> 00:10:21.531  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have to go.

172
00:10:21.971 --> 00:10:25.731  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The festival doesn't start
for an hour.

173
00:10:25.810 --> 00:10:28.890  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But I have to set up the Renewal Scrolls
along the Promenade

174
00:10:28.969 --> 00:10:29.929  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but it won't take long.

175
00:10:30.009 --> 00:10:31.149  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jadzia's promised to help me.

176
00:10:31.169 --> 00:10:32.848  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm. Jadzia, of course.

177
00:10:33.368 --> 00:10:34.407  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've never understood

178
00:10:34.488 --> 00:10:36.727  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
how the two of you
could be such good friends.

179
00:10:36.807 --> 00:10:38.566  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's so...

180
00:10:39.566 --> 00:10:40.806  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Unpredictable.

181
00:10:41.505 --> 00:10:42.166  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And you're so...

182
00:10:42.485 --> 00:10:43.485  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Predictable?

183
00:10:43.565 --> 00:10:45.205  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I didn't mean it like that.

184
00:10:45.284 --> 00:10:48.764  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's just that she gets to spend
so much more time with you than I do.

185
00:10:49.763 --> 00:10:53.362  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Jadzia and I have been doing this
for the past two years.

186
00:10:53.442 --> 00:10:55.281  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's becoming a tradition.

187
00:10:55.361 --> 00:10:58.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I was hoping we could start
a few traditions of our own.

188
00:10:59.153 --> 00:11:01.719  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We will... later tonight.

189
00:11:13.356 --> 00:11:14.516  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

190
00:11:18.355 --> 00:11:20.674  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( exhausted sigh )

191
00:11:22.382 --> 00:11:23.233  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is she asleep?

192
00:11:23.633 --> 00:11:26.592  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It looks like the medicine
Doctor Bashir prescribed is working.

193
00:11:27.031 --> 00:11:28.591  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ooh, that's a relief.

194
00:11:30.231 --> 00:11:31.391  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

195
00:11:32.030 --> 00:11:33.350  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Rough trip?

196
00:11:33.430 --> 00:11:35.589  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, it was a disaster.

197
00:11:36.229 --> 00:11:38.468  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I thought it would never end.

198
00:11:39.724 --> 00:11:40.467  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well...

199
00:11:42.667 --> 00:11:44.027  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm glad you're home.

200
00:11:44.713 --> 00:11:45.586  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Me, too.

201
00:11:46.506 --> 00:11:48.185  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We should get ready for the festival.

202
00:11:48.266 --> 00:11:49.585  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The baby-sitter will be here any minute.

203
00:11:49.665 --> 00:11:51.584  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, the festival.

204
00:11:52.584 --> 00:11:54.384  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
On the other hand...

205
00:11:55.743 --> 00:11:59.672  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We could spend the rest of the day
locked away in our quarters.

206
00:12:00.822 --> 00:12:03.541  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Miles, what I really want to do is sleep.

207
00:12:04.301 --> 00:12:06.780  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well... then maybe you should.

208
00:12:06.860 --> 00:12:08.579  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Miles, I didn't say I was going to.

209
00:12:08.660 --> 00:12:10.299  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I just meant I could use some.

210
00:12:10.379 --> 00:12:11.778  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's OK.

211
00:12:12.418 --> 00:12:15.023  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If you need to sleep, go ahead.

212
00:12:14.217 --> 00:12:17.013  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I'll understand.
-No, you won't.

213
00:12:16.217 --> 00:12:17.297  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You'll be disappointed

214
00:12:17.377 --> 00:12:20.496  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and you'll start brooding
and stomping around like an Andorian bull.

215
00:12:20.576 --> 00:12:23.455  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Look, go or stay, sleep or don't.

216
00:12:23.535 --> 00:12:24.735  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's all the same to me.

217
00:12:24.815 --> 00:12:27.187  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Just tell me what you want to do,
and we'll do it.

218
00:12:27.982 --> 00:12:29.693  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Miles, I've been making decisions
all day long.

219
00:12:29.773 --> 00:12:30.773  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You decide.

220
00:12:32.533 --> 00:12:33.532  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
OK.

221
00:12:34.612 --> 00:12:36.211  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We'll go to the festival

222
00:12:36.532 --> 00:12:38.011  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but we don't have to go right away.

223
00:12:38.549 --> 00:12:41.330  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I mean, you can take time to relax
and then change into something nice.

224
00:12:41.809 --> 00:12:42.970  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nice?

225
00:12:43.689 --> 00:12:44.729  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah.

226
00:12:45.248 --> 00:12:46.608  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Like your red dress.

227
00:12:47.488 --> 00:12:49.607  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My red dress? Really?

228
00:12:50.407 --> 00:12:52.407  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Is there something wrong
with your red dress?

229
00:12:52.886 --> 00:12:56.445  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No. It's, it's...
Just a little tight, that's all.

230
00:12:57.244 --> 00:12:59.484  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh. That's why I like it.

231
00:13:01.643 --> 00:13:04.423  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
All right. If it'll make you happy,
I'll wear the red dress.

232
00:13:04.443 --> 00:13:07.642  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Look, forget the red dress, OK?
Just wear whatever you want.

233
00:13:07.722 --> 00:13:08.961  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Look...

234
00:13:09.181 --> 00:13:12.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's just try to enjoy the next two days.

235
00:13:13.440 --> 00:13:16.959  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'll change into something nice
and we'll go to the festival, OK?

236
00:13:17.678 --> 00:13:18.958  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Fine.

237
00:13:19.039 --> 00:13:20.998  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( door opens, closes )

238
00:13:21.425 --> 00:13:23.717  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs ) I can hardly wait.

239
00:13:29.475 --> 00:13:31.435  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( indistinct conversations )

240
00:13:35.793 --> 00:13:39.364  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( ringing continues )

241
00:13:56.748 --> 00:14:02.506  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( speaking native language )

242
00:14:13.342 --> 00:14:14.542  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( applause )

243
00:14:18.261 --> 00:14:22.019  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And now I have the honor

244
00:14:22.780 --> 00:14:26.538  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
of placing the first
Renewal Scroll into the fire.

245
00:14:29.657 --> 00:14:31.657  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
As the scrolls burn

246
00:14:31.736 --> 00:14:35.295  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
may our troubles turn to ashes with them.

247
00:14:40.654 --> 00:14:43.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( cheering )

248
00:14:46.653 --> 00:14:48.891  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And now, for the next 26 hours

249
00:14:48.972 --> 00:14:52.330  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I expect you all to enjoy yourselves.

250
00:14:52.411 --> 00:14:54.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know I will.

251
00:14:56.289 --> 00:14:58.409  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
May the Prophets walk with us.

252
00:15:05.646 --> 00:15:07.966  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( woodwinds playing )

253
00:15:15.803 --> 00:15:17.405  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groaning )

254
00:15:17.682 --> 00:15:19.182  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jake, are you all right?

255
00:15:19.202 --> 00:15:21.521  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh, just felt funny there for a second.

256
00:15:21.842 --> 00:15:23.681  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're sure you're all right?

257
00:15:24.601 --> 00:15:25.841  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah, Dad.

258
00:15:27.799 --> 00:15:29.519  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Never felt better.

259
00:15:41.436 --> 00:15:43.995  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Bareil? What are you looking for?

260
00:15:44.397 --> 00:15:46.434  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm? Oh, nothing.

261
00:15:46.514 --> 00:15:48.834  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just... just looking.

262
00:15:48.913 --> 00:15:50.033  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm.

263
00:15:50.593 --> 00:15:51.713  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Peldor joi.</i>

264
00:15:51.792 --> 00:15:54.352  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, Jake, how thoughtful. Thank you.

265
00:15:54.432 --> 00:15:57.231  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Uh, I know you're busy
but can I talk to you for a second?

266
00:15:57.311 --> 00:15:58.390  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sure.

267
00:15:58.751 --> 00:16:00.870  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
In private. It's kind of personal.

268
00:16:00.950 --> 00:16:02.389  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, um...

269
00:16:02.470 --> 00:16:04.738  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll be right back.

270
00:16:05.728 --> 00:16:08.148  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now, Jake, what can I do for you?

271
00:16:08.387 --> 00:16:09.667  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh...

272
00:16:10.907 --> 00:16:12.147  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I need some advice.

273
00:16:12.226 --> 00:16:15.466  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You see, there's this older woman
and I think we're perfect for each other.

274
00:16:15.665 --> 00:16:17.865  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah... and she doesn't.

275
00:16:17.945 --> 00:16:19.745  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't know what she thinks.

276
00:16:19.824 --> 00:16:23.543  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, Jake, my advice to you
is to tell Mardah how you feel.

277
00:16:23.623 --> 00:16:25.942  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-That way you'll know--
-Mardah and I broke up.

278
00:16:26.782 --> 00:16:28.502  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You broke up?

279
00:16:28.582 --> 00:16:29.661  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, then, who?

280
00:16:30.341 --> 00:16:31.381  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You.

281
00:16:32.780 --> 00:16:33.860  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Me?

282
00:16:35.645 --> 00:16:36.460  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I love you, Nerys.

283
00:16:38.418 --> 00:16:39.899  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Want to go out with me?

284
00:16:45.736 --> 00:16:46.856  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Morn, it's hard to believe

285
00:16:46.936 --> 00:16:50.375  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
a handsome, fun-loving guy like you
could have so many problems.

286
00:16:50.455 --> 00:16:52.191  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My advice to you is to burn this

287
00:16:52.987 --> 00:16:54.934  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
as quickly as possible
and don't look back.

288
00:17:01.571 --> 00:17:03.011  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sage advice.

289
00:17:03.552 --> 00:17:05.150  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Vedek Bareil. It's good to see you.

290
00:17:05.170 --> 00:17:08.849  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, you have such a wise, generous spirit.

291
00:17:09.929 --> 00:17:11.969  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I only wish I had a friend like you.

292
00:17:12.327 --> 00:17:14.147  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I think of you as a friend.

293
00:17:14.168 --> 00:17:15.408  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You mean that?

294
00:17:15.928 --> 00:17:17.386  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Of course.

295
00:17:17.407 --> 00:17:21.502  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, I'm glad because I was hoping

296
00:17:21.166 --> 00:17:24.205  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that you and I could get
to know each other a little better.

297
00:17:30.003 --> 00:17:31.523  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A lot better.

298
00:17:34.562 --> 00:17:35.962  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Excuse me.

299
00:17:37.521 --> 00:17:39.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( music playing )

300
00:17:59.955 --> 00:18:02.154  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I love Bajoran music.

301
00:18:02.233 --> 00:18:05.653  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's so intelligent, so vital...

302
00:18:05.673 --> 00:18:08.032  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It reminds me of you.

303
00:18:08.761 --> 00:18:10.711  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, dance with me, Odo.

304
00:18:10.790 --> 00:18:13.130  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sorry. I don't dance.

305
00:18:13.150 --> 00:18:14.430  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nonsense.

306
00:18:14.710 --> 00:18:16.669  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I saw you moving to the music.

307
00:18:16.749 --> 00:18:18.589  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That wasn't dancing.

308
00:18:18.668 --> 00:18:20.188  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That was... swaying.

309
00:18:20.268 --> 00:18:21.268  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh...

310
00:18:21.348 --> 00:18:23.227  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
then sway with me, Odo.

311
00:18:23.707 --> 00:18:25.427  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sway with me.

312
00:18:26.026 --> 00:18:29.785  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I just remembered. I'm needed in Security.

313
00:18:30.585 --> 00:18:31.784  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

314
00:18:32.224 --> 00:18:33.664  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll come with you.

315
00:18:34.504 --> 00:18:36.783  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah, hello, Lieutenant.

316
00:18:36.863 --> 00:18:39.182  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Having a good time?
-No.

317
00:18:39.263 --> 00:18:40.782  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( grunts in agreement )

318
00:18:46.780 --> 00:18:48.638  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's right.

319
00:18:48.180 --> 00:18:52.234  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Genuine latinum-plated
Renewal Scroll inscription pens

320
00:18:53.030 --> 00:18:57.020  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
blessed by Vedek Redab himself
shortly before he passed away.

321
00:18:56.217 --> 00:18:57.937  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Each pen is engraved with the words

322
00:18:58.017 --> 00:19:01.296  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
"Deep Space 9's Third Annual
Gratitude Festival,"

323
00:19:01.376 --> 00:19:05.654  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
today's date, and a lovely portrait
of the station by Ermat Zimm.

324
00:19:05.735 --> 00:19:07.774  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, get them while you can!

325
00:19:07.854 --> 00:19:10.453  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're sure to become collectors' items.

326
00:19:10.533 --> 00:19:12.613  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( indistinct conversations )

327
00:19:18.970 --> 00:19:20.290  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh!

328
00:19:27.568 --> 00:19:28.528  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So...

329
00:19:29.647 --> 00:19:32.566  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What do you say we take a walk
around the Promenade for a while?

330
00:19:32.647 --> 00:19:34.486  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'd rather stay here.

331
00:19:34.566 --> 00:19:38.405  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I-I never thought I'd say this
but I kind of miss Quark's.

332
00:19:39.485 --> 00:19:41.723  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The noise, the excitement...

333
00:19:41.804 --> 00:19:42.803  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
our table.

334
00:19:45.349 --> 00:19:46.682  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You know...

335
00:19:46.763 --> 00:19:48.682  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I haven't sat here since you've been gone.

336
00:19:49.521 --> 00:19:52.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, that's so sweet.

337
00:19:53.840 --> 00:19:55.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, how's the survey been going?

338
00:19:56.159 --> 00:19:58.959  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Uh... the terrain's
rougher than we expected

339
00:19:59.038 --> 00:20:01.838  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and the ecosystem's a lot more diverse

340
00:20:01.918 --> 00:20:03.877  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
than it looked from the orbital scans.

341
00:20:03.957 --> 00:20:06.197  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All in all, it's been pretty grueling.

342
00:20:06.276 --> 00:20:07.516  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Really?

343
00:20:07.596 --> 00:20:10.715  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Don't get me wrong.
I'm having a wonderful time.

344
00:20:11.754 --> 00:20:12.754  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's good.

345
00:20:13.394 --> 00:20:16.473  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There is one problem
I have to talk to you about.

346
00:20:16.553 --> 00:20:19.872  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It looks like the project's
taking longer than we hoped.

347
00:20:20.832 --> 00:20:22.831  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What do you mean, "longer"?

348
00:20:23.232 --> 00:20:25.190  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You have to understand, Miles,

349
00:20:25.271 --> 00:20:28.990  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
every valley has
an entirely different ecosystem.

350
00:20:29.340 --> 00:20:30.629  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's a lot of work to be done.

351
00:20:31.732 --> 00:20:33.428  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But how much longer is it going to take?

352
00:20:34.722 --> 00:20:35.627  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm... I'm not sure.

353
00:20:36.319 --> 00:20:37.427  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Try a guess.

354
00:20:37.507 --> 00:20:40.586  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Uh, you know, an extra couple of days?
A week? Two?

355
00:20:40.666 --> 00:20:43.145  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
More like two or three months.

356
00:20:43.545 --> 00:20:44.625  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're telling me

357
00:20:44.705 --> 00:20:47.464  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
you're going to be on Bajor
for another seven months?

358
00:20:48.343 --> 00:20:50.863  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's either that or ask them
to find another botanist.

359
00:20:50.943 --> 00:20:53.222  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maybe that's something worth considering.

360
00:20:53.982 --> 00:20:56.581  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Are you asking me to resign?
-No...

361
00:20:56.661 --> 00:20:59.141  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but seven more months?

362
00:20:59.220 --> 00:21:01.540  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't like this any more than you do.

363
00:21:01.620 --> 00:21:03.379  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You just said you were
having a great time.

364
00:21:03.739 --> 00:21:04.899  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, I'm sorry.

365
00:21:04.979 --> 00:21:07.978  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I suppose you'd be happier
if I were miserable?

366
00:21:08.226 --> 00:21:09.497  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I didn't say that.

367
00:21:12.577 --> 00:21:16.196  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
( sighing ) Sebarr was right.
I never should've mentioned it.

368
00:21:16.855 --> 00:21:18.295  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who's Sebarr?

369
00:21:18.374 --> 00:21:20.374  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He's one of the zoologists
I'm working with.

370
00:21:20.454 --> 00:21:24.578  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He warned me not to talk to you about this
until after the Gratitude Festival.

371
00:21:24.173 --> 00:21:26.971  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And who's he to be giving you advice?

372
00:21:27.612 --> 00:21:28.971  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's a friend.

373
00:21:29.155 --> 00:21:30.331  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A friend?

374
00:21:31.650 --> 00:21:32.930  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I thought you were down there working.

375
00:21:33.450 --> 00:21:34.770  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We are working.

376
00:21:35.249 --> 00:21:38.449  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yeah, with time out for intimate
little chats about our relationship?

377
00:21:39.527 --> 00:21:40.888  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What else did you tell him about us?

378
00:21:42.168 --> 00:21:45.567  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Miles, you're behaving like a child.

379
00:21:45.646 --> 00:21:47.206  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What do you want me to say?

380
00:21:47.286 --> 00:21:50.765  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I want you to say
that you're not going back...

381
00:21:51.285 --> 00:21:53.364  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
that you're going to stay here with me.

382
00:21:54.563 --> 00:21:59.466  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Miles, right now I don't even want
to sit at the same table with you.

383
00:22:00.003 --> 00:22:01.482  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Fine.

384
00:22:01.882 --> 00:22:03.881  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, go on.
Leave.

385
00:22:04.681 --> 00:22:07.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Go back to Bajor and your plants
and Sebarr.

386
00:22:09.679 --> 00:22:10.919  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
See if I care!

387
00:22:36.151 --> 00:22:38.310  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Whoa!
Slow down.

388
00:22:39.511 --> 00:22:40.510  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hi, Dad.

389
00:22:40.990 --> 00:22:42.510  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've been looking all over for you.

390
00:22:42.589 --> 00:22:43.589  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
In case you've forgotten,

391
00:22:43.669 --> 00:22:45.629  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we're hosting a Gratitude Dinner
tonight in the Wardroom.

392
00:22:45.708 --> 00:22:47.468  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I could use your help in getting ready.

393
00:22:47.548 --> 00:22:49.707  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm kind of busy right now, Dad.
I-I have to find someone.

394
00:22:49.788 --> 00:22:51.027  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, Major Kira?

395
00:22:51.387 --> 00:22:53.026  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-How'd you know?
-I just spoke to her.

396
00:22:53.704 --> 00:22:55.305  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Really? Where is she?
-Ah, just hold on!

397
00:22:55.386 --> 00:22:56.865  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But I have to talk to her.

398
00:22:56.945 --> 00:22:59.345  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know, you were right about me
meeting someone at the festival.

399
00:22:59.424 --> 00:23:01.584  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I did not mean Major Kira.

400
00:23:01.664 --> 00:23:04.023  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You like her, don't you?
-Well, of course I like her.

401
00:23:04.673 --> 00:23:05.143  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, so do I.

402
00:23:05.223 --> 00:23:09.621  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
( sighs ) Jake,
what you're feeling now is just a crush.

403
00:23:10.541 --> 00:23:12.340  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Look, Jake...

404
00:23:15.459 --> 00:23:17.219  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Right now,

405
00:23:17.299 --> 00:23:19.939  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
you are confused, vulnerable, hurt.

406
00:23:20.018 --> 00:23:20.978  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You miss Mardah.

407
00:23:21.219 --> 00:23:22.337  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mardah was a mistake.

408
00:23:22.418 --> 00:23:24.697  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She was too young, too immature for me.

409
00:23:25.176 --> 00:23:26.377  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Major Kira is a woman.

410
00:23:26.456 --> 00:23:28.615  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Major Kira is in love with Vedek Bareil.

411
00:23:28.696 --> 00:23:30.815  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It won't last. He's always on Bajor.

412
00:23:31.591 --> 00:23:34.014  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She needs someone who can
be with her all the time, like me.

413
00:23:34.894 --> 00:23:37.853  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
( sighs ) Jake,
I don't want to see you hurt again.

414
00:23:38.253 --> 00:23:39.772  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I appreciate that.

415
00:23:41.167 --> 00:23:42.731  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But this is between Nerys and me.

416
00:23:43.651 --> 00:23:46.490  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Don't worry.
Everything's going to be fine.

417
00:23:46.570 --> 00:23:47.890  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thanks.

418
00:23:50.489 --> 00:23:52.689  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I really can't accept this.

419
00:23:52.768 --> 00:23:54.368  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But I want you to have it.
It's my gift to you.

420
00:23:54.448 --> 00:23:57.847  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, that's very thoughtful of you
but I have nothing to give you in return.

421
00:23:57.927 --> 00:24:00.766  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Being with you is the only present I need.

422
00:24:01.645 --> 00:24:02.925  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now, come on.

423
00:24:03.006 --> 00:24:05.488  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's go write our Renewal Scrolls.

424
00:24:19.320 --> 00:24:21.140  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Peldor joi, </i>Chief.

425
00:24:21.160 --> 00:24:22.959  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You look terrible.

426
00:24:23.479 --> 00:24:24.500  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's just a little headache, that's all.

427
00:24:24.519 --> 00:24:26.740  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Here. Have a free pen.

428
00:24:29.757 --> 00:24:30.797  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What for?

429
00:24:30.877 --> 00:24:33.516  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
To write down your problems
on a Renewal Scroll.

430
00:24:33.596 --> 00:24:35.756  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There isn't a scroll long enough
for all my problems.

431
00:24:35.835 --> 00:24:39.554  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Really? I thought you could sum them up
with one word...

432
00:24:39.634 --> 00:24:40.994  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Keiko.

433
00:24:41.953 --> 00:24:43.353  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tell me I'm wrong.

434
00:24:44.433 --> 00:24:46.593  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If you ask me, it's your own fault.

435
00:24:46.672 --> 00:24:49.192  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You never should have let her
go to Bajor in the first place.

436
00:24:49.271 --> 00:24:51.671  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What was I supposed to do?
Force her to stay here with me?

437
00:24:51.751 --> 00:24:53.710  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That would have been a good start.

438
00:24:53.790 --> 00:24:56.737  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You hu-mans, you never learn.

439
00:24:56.190 --> 00:25:00.708  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You let your women go out in public,
hold jobs,

440
00:25:00.788 --> 00:25:01.908  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
wear clothing,

441
00:25:01.987 --> 00:25:04.227  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and you wonder why your
marriages fall apart.

442
00:25:04.307 --> 00:25:06.146  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's your solution, Quark, huh?

443
00:25:06.226 --> 00:25:08.165  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Treat women like property?

444
00:25:08.186 --> 00:25:09.705  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Criticize it all you want,

445
00:25:09.785 --> 00:25:13.984  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but on the Ferengi homeworld
husbands and wives never argue.

446
00:25:14.304 --> 00:25:17.463  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's no divorce, no broken homes...

447
00:25:17.543 --> 00:25:21.581  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nothing but peaceful conjugal bliss.

448
00:25:22.261 --> 00:25:26.221  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If Ferengi marriages are so wonderful
why are you still single?

449
00:25:27.540 --> 00:25:29.579  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I haven't met the right woman yet.

450
00:25:39.620 --> 00:25:39.980  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, I have.

451
00:25:37.940 --> 00:25:39.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She just walked out that door.

452
00:25:43.000 --> 00:25:47.839  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And out of your life.

453
00:25:47.859 --> 00:25:49.659  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not if I can help it.

454
00:25:59.252 --> 00:26:00.512  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Bareil!

455
00:26:00.533 --> 00:26:02.892  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I was wondering where you disappeared to.

456
00:26:04.211 --> 00:26:06.611  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Come on, you can do better than that.

457
00:26:06.691 --> 00:26:08.810  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Someone might see us.

458
00:26:08.890 --> 00:26:11.570  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We are the only people here.

459
00:26:12.130 --> 00:26:14.608  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Everyone else is on the Promenade.

460
00:26:18.887 --> 00:26:22.687  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We have two hours before we're supposed
to join Commander Sisko for dinner.

461
00:26:24.126 --> 00:26:27.204  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That gives us some time
to be alone together.

462
00:26:27.125 --> 00:26:28.964  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I... I can't. Um...

463
00:26:29.724 --> 00:26:30.764  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why not?

464
00:26:31.124 --> 00:26:32.603  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have to find Jadzia.

465
00:26:33.203 --> 00:26:34.802  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jadzia? Is there something wrong?

466
00:26:34.883 --> 00:26:36.282  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, not at all.

467
00:26:36.722 --> 00:26:37.882  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do you know where she is?

468
00:26:38.842 --> 00:26:41.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's probably on the Promenade.

469
00:26:41.561 --> 00:26:43.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She wasn't there the last time I looked.

470
00:26:43.880 --> 00:26:46.599  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why is it so important
for you to see Jadzia?

471
00:26:47.039 --> 00:26:49.478  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll explain everything later.

472
00:26:50.478 --> 00:26:51.718  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh...

473
00:26:53.197 --> 00:26:54.317  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you, Nerys.

474
00:26:54.676 --> 00:26:55.717  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
For what?

475
00:26:56.036 --> 00:26:57.876  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
For being such a good friend.

476
00:27:02.234 --> 00:27:03.674  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Friend?

477
00:27:06.753 --> 00:27:08.232  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dax...

478
00:27:08.313 --> 00:27:09.512  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
what are you doing here?

479
00:27:09.592 --> 00:27:12.191  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I thought you might need some help
getting ready for the party.

480
00:27:12.271 --> 00:27:15.070  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thanks, but that won't be necessary.

481
00:27:15.150 --> 00:27:17.630  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Wouldn't you rather be celebrating
on the Promenade?

482
00:27:17.709 --> 00:27:20.828  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No, thanks. I don't want to run
into Vedek Bareil.

483
00:27:20.909 --> 00:27:23.748  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, is there a problem between you?

484
00:27:23.828 --> 00:27:25.947  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He can't keep his hands off me.

485
00:27:26.787 --> 00:27:29.066  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That doesn't sound like Vedek Bareil.

486
00:27:29.145 --> 00:27:30.445  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I couldn't believe it myself

487
00:27:30.466 --> 00:27:33.009  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but he wouldn't leave me alone.

488
00:27:32.505 --> 00:27:35.345  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He's probably still out there
looking for me.

489
00:27:35.984 --> 00:27:37.595  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Have you told Kira?

490
00:27:37.595 --> 00:27:35.037  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't know how.

491
00:27:39.035 --> 00:27:40.955  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's going to break her heart.

492
00:27:41.714 --> 00:27:43.834  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs ) Someone has to tell her.

493
00:27:46.553 --> 00:27:48.113  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do you want me to do it?

494
00:27:48.192 --> 00:27:49.272  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Would you?

495
00:27:52.071 --> 00:27:53.351  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well...

496
00:27:54.591 --> 00:27:56.830  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
if you think that's the
best way to handle it.

497
00:27:57.429 --> 00:27:58.229  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

498
00:27:58.309 --> 00:28:00.109  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'd really appreciate it, Benjamin.

499
00:28:00.189 --> 00:28:02.348  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I mean, this whole thing is ridiculous.

500
00:28:03.006 --> 00:28:05.067  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How could I be interested in Bareil?

501
00:28:06.627 --> 00:28:08.267  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We both know...

502
00:28:08.346 --> 00:28:10.266  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's always been you.

503
00:28:15.264 --> 00:28:17.144  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( stammering )

504
00:28:23.502 --> 00:28:24.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dax...

505
00:28:24.981 --> 00:28:26.336  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm?

506
00:28:25.981 --> 00:28:29.500  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What are you doing?
-Making myself comfortable.

507
00:28:31.979 --> 00:28:35.019  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Have I ever told you
that you smell wonderful?

508
00:28:41.737 --> 00:28:47.175  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Ah, you know, old man, I have to admit
you had me going there for a minute.

509
00:28:50.374 --> 00:28:53.813  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Benjamin, stop acting so coy.
There's no one around.

510
00:28:54.613 --> 00:28:56.012  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have an idea.

511
00:28:56.092 --> 00:29:00.730  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You cancel the party, and then, that way
we can spend the evening alone together.

512
00:29:00.811 --> 00:29:03.810  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What do you say?
-Oh... uh...

513
00:29:04.223 --> 00:29:06.449  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Sisko to Bashir.
-BASHIR: <i>Go ahead, Commander.</i>

514
00:29:06.969 --> 00:29:09.168  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Meet me in the Infirmary immediately.

515
00:29:09.248 --> 00:29:10.168  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Aye, sir.</i>

516
00:29:10.727 --> 00:29:12.607  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
BASHIR: Her vital signs are normal.

517
00:29:12.687 --> 00:29:14.526  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Her brain activity is normal.

518
00:29:14.607 --> 00:29:18.086  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No sign of infection or intoxication
of any kind.

519
00:29:18.445 --> 00:29:20.085  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's the picture of health.

520
00:29:20.164 --> 00:29:21.325  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
DAX: Told you.

521
00:29:21.645 --> 00:29:23.364  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then why did you put
your head on my chest?

522
00:29:23.443 --> 00:29:25.204  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, Julian, you should have seen his face.

523
00:29:25.283 --> 00:29:27.842  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Admit it, you were
this far away from total panic.

524
00:29:28.554 --> 00:29:30.242  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
BASHIR: I think we've both been
victims of a practical joke.

525
00:29:30.321 --> 00:29:32.601  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
At least someone around here
has a sense of humor.

526
00:29:34.960 --> 00:29:37.121  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Um, see you at the party, Julian.

527
00:29:45.477 --> 00:29:48.036  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've never been so embarrassed
in all my life,

528
00:29:48.116 --> 00:29:49.636  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
making me go through all those tests.

529
00:29:49.716 --> 00:29:51.715  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's your fault, Dax.
You took this one too far.

530
00:29:51.796 --> 00:29:55.075  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, if I didn't love you so much
I'd be angry with you.

531
00:29:55.154 --> 00:29:56.434  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
See you at the party.

532
00:30:09.430 --> 00:30:11.149  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

533
00:30:12.230 --> 00:30:14.429  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You look like you could use
a little cheering up.

534
00:30:14.509 --> 00:30:16.748  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Jake, do me a favor.
-Anything.

535
00:30:16.827 --> 00:30:17.968  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Leave me alone.

536
00:30:17.988 --> 00:30:19.267  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh...

537
00:30:19.347 --> 00:30:20.667  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

538
00:30:27.784 --> 00:30:29.264  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( door opens )

539
00:30:36.222 --> 00:30:38.061  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Hi, sweetie.
-Hi.

540
00:30:38.301 --> 00:30:40.181  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Feeling better?
-Lots better.

541
00:30:40.261 --> 00:30:42.261  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah, that's what I wanted to hear.

542
00:30:42.340 --> 00:30:43.659  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( snorting )

543
00:30:44.820 --> 00:30:47.658  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Where's Mommy?
-In her room, sad.

544
00:30:48.178 --> 00:30:51.701  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh. Well, listen,
why don't you go and play with Piggy

545
00:30:51.018 --> 00:30:52.457  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
in your room for a while

546
00:30:52.537 --> 00:30:55.296  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and we'll see if Daddy
can cheer Mommy up, huh?

547
00:31:08.372 --> 00:31:10.691  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Keiko, it's me.
Can I come in?

548
00:31:10.772 --> 00:31:12.491  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not now, Miles.

549
00:31:15.370 --> 00:31:19.089  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're right.
I'm an idiot... sometimes.

550
00:31:19.169 --> 00:31:20.449  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If I don't get my own way

551
00:31:20.528 --> 00:31:23.608  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can be selfish
and childish and pigheaded.

552
00:31:24.687 --> 00:31:27.727  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I said some things to you
that were pretty stupid.

553
00:31:28.327 --> 00:31:30.166  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I wish I could take them back.

554
00:31:37.523 --> 00:31:39.723  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But even if it's too late for that, I...

555
00:31:40.483 --> 00:31:43.162  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's one thing
I want you to know, Keiko...

556
00:31:43.242 --> 00:31:44.801  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I... I love you.

557
00:31:45.561 --> 00:31:47.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I always have and I always will.

558
00:31:51.123 --> 00:31:53.159  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I want you to know
I've left a letter of resignation

559
00:31:53.239 --> 00:31:55.278  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
on Commander Sisko's desk.

560
00:31:55.358 --> 00:31:58.277  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm ready to move down to Bajor
with you tomorrow

561
00:31:58.358 --> 00:31:59.717  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
if you'll have me.

562
00:31:59.797 --> 00:32:01.796  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And after that,
if you want to move back to Earth

563
00:32:02.092 --> 00:32:03.435  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
that's OK, too.

564
00:32:03.516 --> 00:32:05.395  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll do whatever it takes.

565
00:32:07.515 --> 00:32:09.274  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I just don't want to lose you.

566
00:32:12.033 --> 00:32:15.454  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Honey, did you hear what I said?

567
00:32:15.633 --> 00:32:16.792  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes.

568
00:32:16.992 --> 00:32:18.232  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And?

569
00:32:19.111 --> 00:32:20.990  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And I need time to think.

570
00:32:22.030 --> 00:32:24.423  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why don't you go
to Commander Sisko's party?

571
00:32:23.990 --> 00:32:26.029  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We can talk when you get back.

572
00:32:29.413 --> 00:32:30.747  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If that's what you want.

573
00:32:35.306 --> 00:32:36.586  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Major...
-Ah!

574
00:32:36.666 --> 00:32:38.825  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Aren't you headed in the wrong direction?

575
00:32:40.105 --> 00:32:42.384  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Commander Sisko's party?
-Oh, I'm not going.

576
00:32:42.464 --> 00:32:45.263  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Why ever not?
-Because Bareil will be there.

577
00:32:45.542 --> 00:32:48.733  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I thought the two of you
were very happy together.

578
00:32:48.753 --> 00:32:51.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So did I, but it turns out
he'd rather be with Dax than me.

579
00:32:51.021 --> 00:32:53.661  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And to make matters worse,
I have Jake Sisko chasing me

580
00:32:53.741 --> 00:32:56.100  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
around the station
professing his undying love.

581
00:32:56.180 --> 00:32:57.179  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
BASHIR: Well, that's strange.

582
00:32:57.260 --> 00:33:00.179  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
A little while ago
Jadzia had Commander Sisko convinced

583
00:33:00.259 --> 00:33:01.259  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
that she was in love with him.

584
00:33:01.338 --> 00:33:03.618  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He even had me examine her
to make sure she was all right.

585
00:33:03.698 --> 00:33:05.497  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Apparently, it was only a joke.

586
00:33:05.577 --> 00:33:07.097  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, are you sure?

587
00:33:07.177 --> 00:33:09.296  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
People are acting very strangely today.

588
00:33:10.194 --> 00:33:13.295  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe I should take another look
at Jadzia's test results.

589
00:33:13.375 --> 00:33:14.334  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Excuse me.

590
00:33:14.415 --> 00:33:17.574  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Constable, would you tell Commander Sisko
that I'll be a little late?

591
00:33:23.651 --> 00:33:26.411  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, I should be getting to the Infirmary.

592
00:33:26.491 --> 00:33:27.810  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll join you.

593
00:33:28.228 --> 00:33:31.809  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
( groans ) Maybe you should examine
Bareil and Jake while you're at it.

594
00:33:32.218 --> 00:33:33.609  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That wouldn't be a bad idea.

595
00:33:36.328 --> 00:33:38.807  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, this won't take long.

596
00:33:52.004 --> 00:33:53.563  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, what is it, Odo?

597
00:33:53.643 --> 00:33:56.322  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I may not be able to read your emotions
but I can read your expression.

598
00:33:56.402 --> 00:33:58.081  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Something's wrong.
-I'm fine.

599
00:33:58.162 --> 00:34:00.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I wish you'd tell me what's bothering you.
Maybe it would help you.

600
00:34:01.135 --> 00:34:03.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As soon as something bothers me
I'll let you know, I promise.

601
00:34:03.720 --> 00:34:05.399  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why do I find stubborn men so attractive?

602
00:34:05.479 --> 00:34:07.118  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groans )

603
00:34:07.199 --> 00:34:08.758  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

604
00:34:08.838 --> 00:34:11.158  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Would you please stop following me?

605
00:34:11.237 --> 00:34:14.077  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, gladly,
if you'll just stop running away.

606
00:34:14.157 --> 00:34:18.835  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I-I-I have something very important
to talk to you about.

607
00:34:19.477 --> 00:34:21.794  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Discuss it with Major Kira.
I'm not interested.

608
00:34:23.754 --> 00:34:25.793  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But, Dad,
you promised that Nerys would be here!

609
00:34:26.063 --> 00:34:28.053  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She will, and stop calling her Nerys.

610
00:34:28.392 --> 00:34:29.432  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( gasps )

611
00:34:29.512 --> 00:34:30.991  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Peldor joi.</i>

612
00:34:31.592 --> 00:34:33.551  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, Commander, I didn't realize

613
00:34:33.631 --> 00:34:35.390  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that you and Lieutenant Dax
were that close.

614
00:34:35.471 --> 00:34:36.390  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're not.

615
00:34:36.470 --> 00:34:38.229  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sisko to Bashir.

616
00:34:39.269 --> 00:34:41.668  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Computer, locate Dr. Bashir.

617
00:34:42.628 --> 00:34:44.707  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
COMPUTER: <i>Dr. Bashir is in the Infirmary.</i>

618
00:34:45.348 --> 00:34:49.546  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
( sighs ) Constable, go get Dr. Bashir
and bring him here immediately.

619
00:34:49.626 --> 00:34:51.346  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll be right back.

620
00:34:51.425 --> 00:34:52.625  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll go with you.

621
00:34:52.705 --> 00:34:54.704  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, of course you will.

622
00:34:57.624 --> 00:34:59.583  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I wonder what Commander Sisko wanted.

623
00:34:59.663 --> 00:35:01.103  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, it can wait.

624
00:35:03.382 --> 00:35:05.301  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is very embarrassing.

625
00:35:05.381 --> 00:35:07.421  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, we have to stop.

626
00:35:08.061 --> 00:35:09.341  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Definitely.

627
00:35:12.419 --> 00:35:13.619  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Doctor!

628
00:35:16.418 --> 00:35:19.497  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Commander Sisko needs to see you
in the Wardroom.

629
00:35:20.057 --> 00:35:21.456  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, tell him...

630
00:35:21.537 --> 00:35:23.376  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, tell him I'll be there shortly.

631
00:35:23.456 --> 00:35:24.496  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now, Doctor!

632
00:35:24.816 --> 00:35:26.055  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You'd better go.

633
00:35:26.135 --> 00:35:27.495  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( moans amorously )

634
00:35:28.014 --> 00:35:29.294  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Right.

635
00:35:33.213 --> 00:35:34.693  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Peldor joi.</i>

636
00:35:38.690 --> 00:35:41.550  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Please, Commander, step aside.

637
00:35:41.570 --> 00:35:43.769  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I need to speak to Jadzia.

638
00:35:43.850 --> 00:35:45.769  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't think she wants to speak with you.

639
00:35:45.849 --> 00:35:47.208  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
DAX: You tell him, Benjamin.

640
00:35:47.649 --> 00:35:49.968  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I... I only want to give her this.

641
00:35:50.368 --> 00:35:52.368  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A Bajoran betrothal bracelet?

642
00:35:52.447 --> 00:35:54.687  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's been in my family for generations.

643
00:35:54.766 --> 00:35:55.846  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Can I see that?

644
00:35:58.445 --> 00:35:59.285  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I...

645
00:35:59.365 --> 00:36:02.245  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nerys! Am I glad to see you.

646
00:36:02.324 --> 00:36:04.182  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Doctor... I need your help!

647
00:36:04.202 --> 00:36:05.983  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And I need yours, too.

648
00:36:06.003 --> 00:36:07.642  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You've got to get me away from Kira.

649
00:36:07.723 --> 00:36:09.722  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can't... ( gasps )
keep my hands off of her.

650
00:36:09.802 --> 00:36:12.161  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What's worse
I can't keep my hands off him.

651
00:36:13.081 --> 00:36:14.281  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( door opens )

652
00:36:16.160 --> 00:36:17.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

653
00:36:19.519 --> 00:36:21.478  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I can't explain it either.

654
00:36:22.518 --> 00:36:24.598  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( gasps )

655
00:36:29.117 --> 00:36:30.636  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

656
00:36:36.514 --> 00:36:38.073  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( <i>sighs </i>)

657
00:36:38.154 --> 00:36:39.833  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She doesn't love me.

658
00:36:40.392 --> 00:36:41.553  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who?

659
00:36:42.072 --> 00:36:43.352  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nerys.

660
00:36:46.031 --> 00:36:47.031  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( <i>sighs </i>)

661
00:36:47.110 --> 00:36:48.711  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're better off.

662
00:36:49.190 --> 00:36:51.669  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
In the end, they only break your heart.

663
00:36:51.750 --> 00:36:53.309  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( door opens )

664
00:36:54.828 --> 00:36:57.810  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Although, sometimes it's worth it.

665
00:37:06.585 --> 00:37:08.145  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What do you think?

666
00:37:08.824 --> 00:37:10.384  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You look beautiful.

667
00:37:11.783 --> 00:37:14.822  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Did you really mean it
about turning in your resignation?

668
00:37:15.355 --> 00:37:15.822  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mm-hmm.

669
00:37:16.462 --> 00:37:20.581  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, you'd better get it back
before Commander Sisko sees it.

670
00:37:21.501 --> 00:37:23.780  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It was very nice of you to offer.

671
00:37:32.058 --> 00:37:34.136  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I love you so much.

672
00:37:39.815 --> 00:37:41.375  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( laughing ) Hey!

673
00:37:42.214 --> 00:37:43.454  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( lasciviously ) Oh...

674
00:37:45.054 --> 00:37:47.253  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ooh...

675
00:37:46.973 --> 00:37:49.852  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Commander, here's that
I'danian spice pudding you ordered.

676
00:37:50.646 --> 00:37:52.531  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I want to give this to you
as a token of my affection.

677
00:37:52.771 --> 00:37:54.010  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, no, you don't!

678
00:37:54.611 --> 00:37:56.650  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Bareil, listen to me...

679
00:37:56.730 --> 00:37:58.689  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll fight for her if I have to!

680
00:38:00.009 --> 00:38:01.288  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( grunts )

681
00:38:05.368 --> 00:38:07.326  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, I'm sorry, Benjamin.

682
00:38:07.407 --> 00:38:09.606  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He was just starting to annoy me.

683
00:38:09.686 --> 00:38:10.646  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
QUARK: Commander...

684
00:38:11.565 --> 00:38:13.805  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You throw one hell of a party.

685
00:38:14.485 --> 00:38:17.404  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Pudding, anyone?
I've got I'danian spice pudding.

686
00:38:17.484 --> 00:38:18.763  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( Bareil groans )

687
00:38:19.643 --> 00:38:21.123  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you all right?

688
00:38:21.643 --> 00:38:23.082  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groans )

689
00:38:23.722 --> 00:38:25.561  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Pudding, anyone?

690
00:38:26.481 --> 00:38:27.841  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Doctor?

691
00:38:28.440 --> 00:38:30.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Pudding, anyone?
-No, no, thank you.

692
00:38:30.479 --> 00:38:31.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ooh!

693
00:38:32.439 --> 00:38:33.439  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groans )

694
00:38:40.677 --> 00:38:42.436  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll take one.

695
00:38:43.076 --> 00:38:44.595  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Help yourself.

696
00:38:46.475 --> 00:38:48.275  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why did she hit me?

697
00:38:48.794 --> 00:38:50.314  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( gasps )

698
00:38:50.954 --> 00:38:52.593  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, forget about him.

699
00:38:52.674 --> 00:38:55.833  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What about me? I need you, Keiko.

700
00:38:56.512 --> 00:38:58.631  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My ears tingle at the sight of you.

701
00:38:58.712 --> 00:39:00.071  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Marry me.

702
00:39:00.151 --> 00:39:01.790  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's taken, Quark!

703
00:39:02.027 --> 00:39:03.310  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( squealing )

704
00:39:03.389 --> 00:39:04.969  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Easy, Chief.

705
00:39:04.990 --> 00:39:06.789  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He doesn't know what he's doing.

706
00:39:10.148 --> 00:39:12.399  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you looking at me for?

707
00:39:12.307 --> 00:39:15.746  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Zanthi fever?
Oh, that's ridiculous.

708
00:39:15.827 --> 00:39:17.306  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That, that's impossible.

709
00:39:17.385 --> 00:39:19.025  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That only affects older Betazoids.

710
00:39:19.105 --> 00:39:21.064  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, that may be,
but according to my tests

711
00:39:21.145 --> 00:39:22.966  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
you show all the symptoms.

712
00:39:23.771 --> 00:39:26.103  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Zanthi fever is a virus
which affects the empathic abilities of...

713
00:39:26.183 --> 00:39:28.583  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
um... mature Betazoids.

714
00:39:28.662 --> 00:39:31.182  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It causes them to project
their emotions onto others.

715
00:39:31.661 --> 00:39:35.581  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then Mrs. Troi's amorous feelings
for... someone on the station

716
00:39:35.660 --> 00:39:37.420  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
were being passed along
to the people around her?

717
00:39:37.500 --> 00:39:38.460  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, not everyone.

718
00:39:38.539 --> 00:39:40.978  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Only those within close proximity to her
when she had an attack,

719
00:39:41.059 --> 00:39:42.458  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and even then
there would have had to have been

720
00:39:42.538 --> 00:39:44.738  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
some preexisting latent attraction.

721
00:39:45.578 --> 00:39:48.976  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You're saying Dax...
-Only on a subconscious level.

722
00:39:49.336 --> 00:39:51.496  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Best not think about it too much,
if you ask me.

723
00:39:52.136 --> 00:39:54.295  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I am terribly sorry, Commander.

724
00:39:54.375 --> 00:39:56.494  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I hope I haven't caused too much trouble.

725
00:39:56.574 --> 00:39:59.533  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm sure no permanent harm
was done, right, Doctor?

726
00:39:59.613 --> 00:40:02.372  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, a simple wide-spectrum antiviral agent
should cure Mrs. Troi.

727
00:40:02.453 --> 00:40:03.532  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And as for everyone else

728
00:40:03.612 --> 00:40:04.971  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
well, they'll be back to normal
in a day or two.

729
00:40:05.052 --> 00:40:06.091  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Excuse me.

730
00:40:06.851 --> 00:40:09.370  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I promised Nerys that I'd meet her
in her quarters this evening.

731
00:40:10.650 --> 00:40:14.169  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I think you ought to postpone that visit
for a day or two.

732
00:40:14.968 --> 00:40:16.328  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sigh )

733
00:40:17.567 --> 00:40:19.847  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
SISKO: <i>Commander's Log, supplemental.</i>

734
00:40:20.597 --> 00:40:22.207  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I'm happy to report </i>
<i>that Dr. Bashir's diagnosis</i>

735
00:40:22.286 --> 00:40:23.806  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>has been proven correct.</i>

736
00:40:24.183 --> 00:40:27.045  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>My son and all the others affected</i>
<i>by Mrs. Troi's condition </i>

737
00:40:27.125 --> 00:40:29.124  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>have made full recoveries.</i>

738
00:40:29.204 --> 00:40:30.324  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( Troi laughing )

739
00:40:30.404 --> 00:40:34.002  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This is one Gratitude Festival
they'll be talking about for a long time.

740
00:40:34.083 --> 00:40:35.842  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know I'll never forget it.

741
00:40:37.143 --> 00:40:39.761  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I hope everything
works out for you, Odo...

742
00:40:39.841 --> 00:40:41.321  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
with Major Kira.

743
00:40:41.401 --> 00:40:43.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I... don't know what you mean.

744
00:40:43.360 --> 00:40:46.639  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, don't worry.
Your secret's safe with me.

745
00:40:46.719 --> 00:40:49.079  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
After all, I know what it's like

746
00:40:49.158 --> 00:40:53.477  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to be attracted to someone who doesn't
necessarily feel the same way.

747
00:40:56.716 --> 00:40:58.516  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

748
00:40:58.595 --> 00:41:01.034  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If you get tired of waiting for her...

749
00:41:11.191 --> 00:41:13.039  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
...you know where to find me.

750
00:41:15.835 --> 00:41:16.430  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll keep that in mind.

751
00:41:23.268 --> 00:41:26.627  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So, you're sure Dr. Bashir said
your test results were negative?

752
00:41:26.707 --> 00:41:28.986  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's right.
My headache was just a headache.

753
00:41:29.066 --> 00:41:30.986  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I never was affected by Mrs. Troi.

754
00:41:31.065 --> 00:41:35.545  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I guess that means you don't have
a latent attraction to me, after all.

755
00:41:35.624 --> 00:41:37.264  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nothing latent about it

756
00:41:37.343 --> 00:41:39.023  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
or weren't you paying
attention last night?

757
00:41:39.104 --> 00:41:40.957  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I was paying attention.

758
00:41:41.502 --> 00:41:43.702  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You still have the touch, O'Brien.

759
00:41:46.662 --> 00:41:48.500  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So do you.

760
00:41:53.419 --> 00:41:55.338  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You take good care of Mommy, honey, OK?

761
00:41:55.419 --> 00:41:57.058  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I will.

762
00:42:05.416 --> 00:42:06.815  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We'll see you in a few months.

763
00:42:07.278 --> 00:42:08.214  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll be here.

764
00:42:16.372 --> 00:42:17.612  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Chief?

765
00:42:20.810 --> 00:42:22.210  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( both laughing )

